  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Disaster Resilient Future: Mobilising Comm. &amp; Inst. for Effective Risk Reduction</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is part of DIPECHO VI action plan for South Asia and will contribute to NARRI consortium joint project on DRR in Bangladesh through ECHO funding. The project will mainly focus on flood and Earthquake hazards with the key components  - capacity building of CBOs and LGIs on risk assessment and reduction measures, mass community mobilisation and awareness on safe DRR practices, small scale risk mitigation and advocacy both at national and local level to promote linkages of development with DRR and effective functioning of institutional and policy setup in Bangladesh as far as DRR is concerned.</narrative>
  </description>
